<p><div class="left-margin" id="set-B"><h2>Soft Skills Learnt in IT major</h2></div></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Logical thinking</strong>: Learn requirements and outputs.</p>

    <p>You can learn to perform a function in a logical order, with the realization of required final outputs. This kind of thinking can be obtained in a simple function as well. <br />For example, if you want to print a pyramid, after asking user input of its height. You need to well define the orders of the executions, and assign the variable to the logical functions. You can be trained to think during the process.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Be patient</strong>: There are a lot of failures.</p>

    <p>I was so frustrated at the beginning, about the amount of failures to a simple programming assignment. However, it is quite normal to encounter problems with new programming languages. It is required to find solutions in a better pace with calm, so the patience is trained.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Generate Results</strong>: Follow Rules</p>

    <p>There are some rules exisiting in programming, so the codes can be interpreted to the computer, and start working. Programmer may know the underlying things, but the users can observe the user interface, or so-called outputs only. 
 This leads myself thinking of the skills of painting. It is about to make the painted objects looking good under some rules, such as sunshine, or air reflection. This mindset allows myself to learn new skills better.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

